main event: An unidentified flying object was observed in Williamsport, Pennsylvania, on April 23, 1969, lasting for 25 seconds.
interesting points: The object was described as shiny silver/white and silent., It gradually disappeared from view and moved behind clouds before reappearing., Other witnesses were present but could not corroborate details., The UFO appeared to float without any visible means of propulsion., It was reportedly about the size of a car and very rapid in movement.
sighted object: A shiny silver/white object in the sky
witness description: One reliable witness and others present who did not contribute detailed accounts.
